The paper proposes a learning framework for domain transfer learning based on both instances and attributes, using a shared convolutional neural network (CNN) to embed the attributes of different domains. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computational linguistics (cs.CL), and multimedia (cs.MM). Among these, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely categories as they are directly related to the proposed learning framework.
